lass="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65493"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65493">Myths of the ages of the world</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65494"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65494">Myths of the gods</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65495"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65495">Myths of heroes</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65496"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65496">Myths of seasonal renewal</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65497"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65497">Myths involving animal transformations</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref65498"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Types-of-myths-in-Greek-culture#ref65498">Other types</a></li></ul></li><li data-target="#ref65499"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Greek-mythology/Greek-mythological-characters-and-motifs-in-art-and-literature">Greek mythological characters and motifs in art and literature</a></li></ul></div>
